Implement the chosen access-control design and verify it end-to-end with realistic scenarios: coder sessions can modify $REPOROOT but cannot edit plan structure/descriptions in $PLANROOT; planner sessions can edit the plan but cannot modify $REPOROOT; status/progress changes happen only via `aap-*` (and only when allowed). Verification should include concrete commands and expected error messages, ensuring that “read-only filesystem” outcomes are treated as intentional and do not trigger attempts to bypass restrictions.
